Italian Diesel-Carrying Vessel Seized in Gulf of Guinea, Xinhua Reports

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-07-24T15:09:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/italian-diesel-carrying-vessel-seized-in-gulf-of-guinea-xinhua-reports.html
Pirates seized an Italian ship
carrying diesel off the coast of the West African nation of
 Benin , Xinhua reported, citing the Italian Foreign Ministry.  The vessel, whose crew includes two Italians, 20 Filipinos
and a Romanian captain, was seized in the Gulf of Guinea earlier
today, the news agency said. Three pirates boarded the ship,
named Rbd Anima e Core, and took control of it, Xinhua said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  